Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you mystery fans hear "triplets",
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.01,0:00:09.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,what comes to mind is probably a substitution trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.46,0:00:12.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure enough, this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.51,0:00:16.26,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.26,0:00:19.10,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}With brilliant detective skills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:21.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A villa connected with the Suzuki Financial Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.05,0:00:23.26,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's someone suspicious among a group of triplets!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.26,0:00:25.00,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.92,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.92,0:00:29.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:17.36,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Izu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.38,0:02:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Summer! You got your sun and your ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:26.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't believe Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s the only boy on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.02,0:02:30.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when there's two hot girls here! How pathetic...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.17,0:02:32.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:36.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously! This is your villa's private beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.76,0:02:38.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.27,0:02:43.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here to get a great tan\Nand catch guys all summer long!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.09,0:02:47.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always talking about guys, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.59,0:02:51.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be nice to know who your husband'll be!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.45,0:02:55.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You bought that swimsuit\Nto show Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.30,0:03:01.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That... was for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:04.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Since I'm here, I'll get a closer look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.83,0:03:09.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.32,0:03:10.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Young girls are so nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:14.77,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo Tomizawa (28)\NAyako's Fiancée
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.28,0:03:13.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have gotten engaged yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.27,0:03:18.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you! You're supposed to be in love with my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.84,0:03:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.87,0:03:26.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo Tomizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, third son of the\Nhead of the Tomizawa Financial Group!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.25,0:03:28.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's marrying my sister in the fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.19,0:03:32.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our two family companies are really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:34.75,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Family Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:34.75,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Family Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:35.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Even our villas are next to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.78,0:03:40.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He saw my sister at a party and had love at first sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.69,0:03:43.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're embarrassing me, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:47.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in our villa if you're looking for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:52.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm here to introduce her\Nto my father and brothers...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.49,0:03:54.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So then—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.42,0:03:55.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:58.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. My brothers arrive tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:00.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but my father should be at the villa by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.94,0:04:03.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.65,0:04:09.97,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the Tomizawa residence.\NWe're not home right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.97,0:04:14.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so please leave a message after the beep—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:15.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's the machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.26,0:04:17.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.26,0:04:19.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.04,0:04:22.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird. He was supposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:24.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:28.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuhara-{\i1}ojisama{\i0} is coming!\NThis is no time to play in the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:30.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to greet him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.36,0:04:31.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.61,0:04:35.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.77,0:04:36.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dad...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.36,0:04:43.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! I said to wait in the villa for me to bring her there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.11,0:04:45.41,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuhara Tomizawa (60)\NPresident of Tomizawa Financial Group
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.57,0:04:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we might enjoy your\Nfuture wife's cooking tonight...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.36,0:04:48.28,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako Suzuki\NSonoko's Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:50.18,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sent it flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:57.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's gone! Three runs! Kogure sent it\Ninto the right stands in the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:58.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.57,0:05:01.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. You're sure a big Kogure fan...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.80,0:05:03.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure am!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.30,0:05:05.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn't have to watch him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:11.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice. I'm getting bad satellite reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:16.42,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A pop fly down the center!\NThe Falcons are on fire now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.60,0:05:22.46,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's 9:00, so we bring you a 5-minute news break!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:27.93,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Typhoon 11 has intensified and\Nis moving northward from Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:31.96,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As a result, many planes and boats are delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:30.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9:00? It's only the 6th inning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.60,0:05:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rain kept delaying the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.85,0:05:36.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Might you have a radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:40.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like that game's on the radio...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:46.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! It'll begin soon!\NHow about some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:51.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki women are so considerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.42,0:05:54.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo! You're one lucky guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.63,0:05:57.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My other two sons, on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.35,0:06:04.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi, the oldest, ditched the business\Nand became a novelist instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.42,0:06:06.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's still single.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.15,0:06:09.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuji, the middle son, joined the company
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.08,0:06:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but got engaged with some\Nnobody without my consent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.29,0:06:15.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking bad about them...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:19.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Yuzo! With your stupid paintings and all...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:21.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:27.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in my studio. I have an illustration to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:28.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.79,0:06:31.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If only he'd quit being stubborn and join the business,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.70,0:06:34.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd give him a good position!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:45.32,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's over! The Falcons finally win 9-8 in the 11th inning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.59,0:06:46.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Alright! Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.64,0:06:49.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This{\i0} is the essence of Falcons baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:06:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look at the time. I should get back to my villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:07:01.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I'll bring my sons over tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:03.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.51,0:07:04.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:10.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! I wonder if he plans to watch\Nanother night game tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:16.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's already 11:30. We should—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.62,0:07:18.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, a power failure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:20.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:24.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The lights are out in the other villa too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:26.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been the lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.55,0:07:30.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:32.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:33.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:34.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.47,0:07:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.85,0:07:45.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.81,0:07:47.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.57,0:07:52.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:08:00.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Darn it! I lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.34,0:08:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:07.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:15.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}W-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.29,0:08:21.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.96,0:08:26.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you witnessed Mr. Tomizawa\Nbeing beaten to death by his son Yuzo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.71,0:08:29.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at 11:30 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:30.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.78,0:08:35.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. What's all this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.96,0:08:36.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.32,0:08:39.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo Tomizawa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.71,0:08:40.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.94,0:08:41.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.53,0:08:46.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know full well you killed your own father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.03,0:08:49.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Dad?! That's crazy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.05,0:08:53.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Let go! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:54.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on, Yuzo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.03,0:08:59.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuji Tomizawa (28)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:57.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuji-{\i1}niisan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:08:59.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.17,0:09:04.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-aniki{\r}! Looks like something happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.79,0:09:07.67,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi Tomizawa (28)\NNovelist
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.10,0:09:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing. I need an idea for a new novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:10.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}T-Triplets?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.50,0:09:15.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo Tomizawa! You're under arrest for the murder of your father, Mr. Tetsuhara Tomizawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.65,0:09:18.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Officer! Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:21.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We did see the killer's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.51,0:09:25.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But we only saw his eyes and nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.60,0:09:31.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't know Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had two identical twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.77,0:09:36.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it was one of you three...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.24,0:09:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in Okinawa last night on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.27,0:09:45.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I took the first flight out\Nand landed at Haneda 3 hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:49.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The last flight to Okinawa leaves at 8:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:52.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have been at the villa when it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mr. Officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.27,0:09:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I can call it an alibi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.29,0:10:00.41,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You have two messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:03.06,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:05.00,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:08.52,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's weird. He was supposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:11.64,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}3:10 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.64,0:10:15.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was me! I used my cell phone to call him from the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.54,0:10:17.16,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hello, this is Taichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.70,0:10:18.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:22.59,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.59,0:10:27.09,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kogure pulled that homer to the\Nright in the bottom of the 6th!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.09,0:10:30.78,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a batter! Well, see you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.69,0:10:34.55,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}11:34 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,11:34 PM... The time the murder took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:44.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're certain it happened around 11:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.21,0:10:49.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I had checked the clock before we saw the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:55.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he did it!\NThat game was only on satellite!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:10:58.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It ended just after 11:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have known how it ended\Nunless he watched it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:05.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirm that with the TV and radio stations! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:05.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:09.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, if neither of us is the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.69,0:11:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo's the only possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.92,0:11:13.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.51,0:11:15.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'd never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.83,0:11:17.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where were you last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:20.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my studio the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:26.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! A fellow illustrator called\Nand woke me up! Just after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.92,0:11:28.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He woke you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.59,0:11:29.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.38,0:11:33.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dozed off! I had to pull an\Nall-nighter to finish this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.54,0:11:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll check with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yokomizo! About that passenger list...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.31,0:11:47.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? My name was there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:50.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:53.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The issue is the time the plane landed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:12:00.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The plane you were supposedly on\Nlanded at Haneda 30 minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:01.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the typhoon delayed it!\NThey said so on the news last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.86,0:12:07.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.82,0:12:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you tell us where\Nyou {\i1}really{\i0} were last night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:18.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tokyo...! That's right!\NI returned to Tokyo last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:19.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To Hiromi's place in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:21.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.28,0:12:26.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My fiancée. I was worried because\NI heard she had collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.26,0:12:30.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I'd catch hell if my old man\Nfound out I'd dropped work for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.24,0:12:31.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I had someone cover for me in Okinawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.49,0:12:34.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:36.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone vouch for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:36.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.98,0:12:40.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I just mentioned how the game ended!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.87,0:12:45.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No news programs were covering it at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.19,0:12:49.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, because I flipped channels,\Nhoping to see that home run again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.70,0:12:53.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yokomizo. He's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:58.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after midnight when TV\Nand radio stations covered the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.67,0:13:01.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, are you a fan of Kogure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:05.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were praising him on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.02,0:13:11.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's awesome! Only he could hit\Na home run into the right stands!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit?! Explain yourself, Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.18,0:13:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said he pulled it to the right on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:21.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you {\i1}really{\i0} watching that game?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:24.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess the truth's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:26.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}you{\i0} killed your father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:34.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort! I meant that\NI didn't see the game on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.07,0:13:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I listened to it all on the radio\Nwhile playing pachinko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:42.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was taking a break from working on my novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.00,0:13:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the only radio broadcast\Nwas in Osaka, where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.61,0:13:51.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, only one radio station\Nin Osaka aired that game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.78,0:13:56.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who is it?! One of those three is lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:14:01.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the victim's missing watch bugs me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.30,0:14:03.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why would the killer take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.55,0:14:06.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}To keep the time a secret? Or—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:09.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This VCR is blinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:14.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's because of the 10-minute\Nblackout that happened at 11:30 last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:18.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, yeah! There was a blackout just before the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:19.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A blackout?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.10,0:14:23.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait, this is strange! What he said is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.89,0:14:26.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And at the time, it was—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.56,0:14:29.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Then the watch taken from the victim was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:31.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:37.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No doubt about it! The killer is the one telling two lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.33,0:14:46.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to ask all three of you\Nto come down to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:49.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.08,0:14:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:52.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.38,0:14:53.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:59.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These folks saw the killer's face\Njust after the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.79,0:15:02.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One that looked just like you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:08.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, one of you killed your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.06,0:15:14.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I know who did it! It's definitely\Nthe one with the strange alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:18.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Alright! I'll knock Sonoko out\Nand make her a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.31,0:15:21.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:24.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this watch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.34,0:15:25.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:27.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:30.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was aiming a weird watch at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:35.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a toy! Dr. Agasa gave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:38.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A BB comes out if you press a button!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:40.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a troublemaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:42.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta use the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:54.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?! Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.87,0:15:56.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:16:00.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that he killed Tetsuhara-{\i1}ojisama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.05,0:16:06.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one of the three has a clear alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.62,0:16:11.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's one who's clearly lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:13.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.39,0:16:14.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.39,0:16:17.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.71,0:16:18.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:21.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was in an Osaka pachinko parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I could've been here then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:27.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A pachinko parlor at 11:30, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.33,0:16:29.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.81,0:16:35.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know that pachinko parlors
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,can only stay open until 11:00 PM?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:45.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, pachinko parlors are generally\Nforbidden to operate past 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:47.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.76,0:16:50.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.04,0:16:52.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.49,0:16:56.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the broadcast in a taxi\Non my way home from the parlor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:16:57.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.88,0:17:00.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be like that. It was a simple mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:06.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I left a message when the murder took place!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.29,0:17:08.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.18,0:17:09.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.27,0:17:14.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the major oversight\Nyou made during the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.04,0:17:16.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.82,0:17:19.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know; you were there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.88,0:17:23.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The power went out for 10 minutes at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.43,0:17:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The answering machine\Nwouldn't work without power!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:32.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Its batteries power the clock,\Nbut it can't record messages!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:37.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's your message doing there at 11:34?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.69,0:17:42.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you could ask Yuzo the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.05,0:17:45.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he got a call just after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.66,0:17:48.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.16,0:17:51.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can still make calls during a power outage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:58.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. Telephones receive\Npower through the phone lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:02.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Someone must've messed\Nwith the clock to frame me—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.67,0:18:05.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling when you'd call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.31,0:18:10.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody could've matched the times just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.27,0:18:13.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, when the game ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:17.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you left a message on the machine whose\Nclock you had set ahead in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:20.87,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.87,0:18:24.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if you left the message just\Nwhen the murder happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.49,0:18:29.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you turned the clock back,\Nand waited for your father to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.43,0:18:34.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father, who came next door to see the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:37.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you killed him when he came back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:42.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't have known when he'd return...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:47.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you knew. You used a transmitter to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:48.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A transmitter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.27,0:18:52.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bugged your villa?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:56.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then go ahead and look! There won't be any!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.73,0:18:59.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody said you bugged the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.63,0:19:03.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there something unnaturally\Nmissing from the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:05.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:08.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! With a bugged watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.86,0:19:12.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he could keep tabs on both the victim and the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.18,0:19:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the watch was taken to remove the evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.91,0:19:18.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bugging the victim's watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:27.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and breaking his satellite receiver\Nto make him come to my villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:31.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As his son, you could easily do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.78,0:19:36.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice theory. I almost want to use it for a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:41.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be a third-rate novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.28,0:19:44.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any proof that I changed\Nthe answering machine's clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.66,0:19:51.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The times match; even Yuzo's\Nmessage had the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.99,0:19:54.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk big for having no proof—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playin' around!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.30,0:20:00.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fake time and message on the answering machine
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:04.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,actually prove that you're the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.63,0:20:08.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Brother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.20,0:20:08.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be true...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:11.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! This must be a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:14.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had no reason to kill Dad...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:19.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, Yuzo. I'm not\Nthe great brother you take me for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:23.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Money. I wanted the old man's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:25.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I could keep writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:30.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Things got tough. I suddenly\Nran out of work and money...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:35.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out when I went to Dad for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.59,0:20:40.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had pressured the publishers\Nto drop each job that came my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:47.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he wanted me to quit\Nand follow in his footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.34,0:20:48.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So then you—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:54.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I used his visit here to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:21:00.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's also why I sent him the\Nbugged watch and broke his receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.34,0:21:06.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo. I was going to try pinning it on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To increase my share of the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:14.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all so I could keep writing my novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.19,0:21:17.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems I wrote a poor mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.91,0:21:21.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To think the power would go out just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:26.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess fact is stranger than fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.03,0:21:32.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I didn't have the skill to be a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.93,0:23:00.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with Sonoko? She's spacing out...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.01,0:23:03.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's probably relieved Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.25,0:23:08.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Uh oh. She's staring at her arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:11.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me she noticed\NI shot a sleeping dart in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.80,0:23:14.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.87,0:23:17.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about? That was great detective work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.62,0:23:18.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective work?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.19,0:23:20.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.96,0:23:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally white!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.69,0:23:28.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to get a tan and catch some guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.21,0:23:33.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Ran! Let's go to a tanning salon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.68,0:23:37.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not now! We have to give our statements at the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.48,0:23:39.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.66,0:23:42.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a dumb girl...
